<Author>PeepsPiper
<Content>Excellent value We stayed here on 19 August 2004 and this little hotel was excellent value at 45 Euro for the night (an internet rate).The room and bathroom were a good size. The room was basic but had everything needed, including tv - just not air-conditioning. But that was okay - there were large windows that we opened for relief, as the night was a bit humid.The hotel is relatively close to a couple of metro stations (about a 5 minute walk) and therefore it's easy enough to make your way around. It was about 10 minutes on the metro from Zoo Station. There are eateries close by to the hotel, a convenience store across the road and supermarkets around the corner. Also a self service laundry close by.The area is quiet and peaceful, the hotel is in good shape and the staff were friendly. For the price it was excellent value and is recommended. 
